Iraq accepted some and refused other weapons inspections. In 1997, they expelled all US members of the inspection team, alleging that the United States was using the inspections as a front for espionage, which the U.S. later admitted was true. The inspection team returned for a period between 1997 and 1999, when it was replaced by a new team which began inspections in 2002.<br>
